text.__SUMMARY__: Conus balabacensis is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones.These snails are predatory and venomous. They are capable of "stinging" humans.
text.Description: The size of the shell varies between 15 mm and 29 mm.
text.Distribution: This marine species  occurs off Sabah, Malaysia and Palawan, Philippines
